The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | International | Pak agent shot dead
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Pak agent shot dead
                            
	Islamabad, April 11 (Reuters): Gunmen riding a car shot dead an intelligence agent in a northwestern Pakistani town today, the third official from the governments security agency to be killed in little over two weeks, police said.        
	The official, Khaliq Khan, head of the Intelligence Bureau in Charsadda town, was killed on his way home after Friday prayers. Two other officials from the bureaus anti-terrorism wing were killed in Karachi on March 27.        
	The men in a red coloured car sprayed bullets on Khan as he walked along a road killing him on the spot, a police official, Mohammad Iftikhar said.        
	The motive of the killing was not immediately known, which took place in a region where pro-Taliban Pakistani militants are very active.        
	Another official of the same agency was killed in Charsadda a few months ago and the militants had claimed responsibility for the attack.        
	Media curbs lifted        
	Pakistans new government made its first legislative move to reverse President Pervez Musharraf state of emergency dictates, introducing a bill today to lift curbs on the media.                                                                                                                                                                            
